den wall on the left, and large glass windows on the right. The space leads to a wooden door at the far end.\" width=\"810\" height=\"1080\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/Red-Rock-House-Nevada-Faulkner-Architects-6-810x1080.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/Red-Rock-House-Nevada-Faulkner-Architects-6-800x1067.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/Red-Rock-House-Nevada-Faulkner-Architects-6-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/Red-Rock-House-Nevada-Faulkner-Architects-6-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/Red-Rock-House-Nevada-Faulkner-Architects-6.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/the-red-rock-house-is-an-architectural-dialogue-with-the-desert/red-rock-house-nevada-faulkner-architects-7/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-559155\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/Red-Rock-House-Nevada-Faulkner-Architects-7-810x608.jpg\" alt=\"Modern bedroom with large floor-to-ceiling windows, a double bed, contemporary art on the walls, and minimalist furnishings. View of a mountainous landscape outside.\" width=\"810\" height=\"608\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/Red-Rock-House-Nevada-Faulkner-Architects-7-810x608.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/Red-Rock-House-Nevada-Faulkner-Architects-7-800x600.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/Red-Rock-House-Nevada-Faulkner-Architects-7-768x576.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/Red-Rock-House-Nevada-Faulkner-Architects-7.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe material palette of the Red Rock House is intentionally restrained, relying on local materials that connect the building to its surroundings. The use of locally sourced sand, gravel, and fly ash to create concrete for the floors and walls gives the structure a natural buff hue that resonates with the distant mountains. These materials were chosen not just for their aesthetic qualities but also for their ability to endure the desert conditions. In the intense desert light, the concrete takes on a warm, sunlit tone that changes throughout the day.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/the-red-rock-house-is-an-architectural-dialogue-with-the-desert/red-rock-house-nevada-faulkner-architects-8/\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-559156\" data-wpel-link=\"internal\"\u003e\u003cimg loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/Red-Rock-House-Nevada-Faulkner-Architects-8-810x1080.jpg\" alt=\"Modern bathroom with wood paneling, marble walls, large mirror, and glass shower enclosure. A small round chair sits in the middle of the room.\" width=\"810\" height=\"1080\" srcset=\"https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/Red-Rock-House-Nevada-Faulkner-Architects-8-810x1080.jpg 810w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/Red-Rock-House-Nevada-Faulkner-Architects-8-800x1067.jpg 800w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/Red-Rock-House-Nevada-Faulkner-Architects-8-768x1024.jpg 768w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/Red-Rock-House-Nevada-Faulkner-Architects-8-1152x1536.jpg 1152w, https://design-milk.com/images/2024/10/Red-Rock-House-Nevada-Faulkner-Architects-8.jpg 1280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 810px) 100vw, 810px\"/\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe upper-level sleeping areas are housed within a framework of perforated weathering steel. This screen not only protects the interior from the sun but also provides a measure of privacy while allowing for natural ventilation. The perforations in the steel create a dappled effect of light and shadow, adding a dynamic quality to the interior spaces as the sun moves across the sky.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://design-milk.com/